this part of your code is still asynchronously run
```java
test.then(function(result) {
    output = result;
})
```
so the ```java console.log()``` will fire before this callback is fired and the output variable has the data from the result callback function parameter.

to solve this just put the console.log() inside the .then() function&#39;s callback paramater

```java 
test.then(function(result) {
    output = result;
    console.log(output); 
})
```

